text: White Rose () is a 1919 Hungarian drama movie directed by Alexander Korda and based on the 1853 novel by Mór Jókai. It stars María Corda, Gyula Bartos, Emil Fenyvessy, and Helene von Bolvary. ==Other websites== * Category:1919 drama movies Category:Hungarian silent movies Category:Movies directed by Alexander Korda
